The paper deals with approximation algorithms for optimization problems related to graphs and trees, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The use of primal-dual algorithms and linear programming relaxations suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The study of approximation ratios and bicriteria algorithms suggests that it could belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the use of logarithmic approximations and analysis of tradeoffs suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
